    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"276935\">@Simon Willerton</span>, what do you think of taking the dual of a convex space to be the space of all convex-linear functions to <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">R</mi><mo>ˉ</mo></mover></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\bar{\\mathbb{R}}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8256699999999999em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.8256699999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathbb\">R</span></span><span style=\"top:-3.25789em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"accent-body\" style=\"left:-0.16666em;\"><span class=\"mord\">ˉ</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>?</p>",
